; offline-nl-translation-training.form — how to train OUR OWN Form-native NL→NL
; model OFFLINE, from content already on disk, with copyright-restricted material
; held to TESTING only (never the training fold).
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-18):
;   "Document how we can locally train NL→NL our own Form-native model when we have
;    content already downloaded. We need an offline training mode that can train. We
;    can use copyrighted material for TESTING, since we cannot train on them."
;
; This is a how-to + assembly cell. The pieces already exist and are proven; this
; names the offline path through them and adds the one missing safeguard — the
; lawful-to-train gate — so the legal boundary is enforced, not just intended.
;
; ── WHAT "OFFLINE" MEANS HERE ──
;   - No network during training. The corpus is files already on disk
;     (~/.coherence-network/form-cli-corpus/corpus.jsonl is the live example — the
;     body's own 949+ captured oracle turns, 22 MB, downloaded once).
;   - The TEACHER is local. oracle-catalog.fk's local rows (whisper.cpp on-device,
;     a local LLM) are replaceable on-device teachers; no consent membrane is
;     crossed for a local oracle (trust = "local"). Remote oracles are a separate,
;     consented path and are NOT part of offline training.
;   - The COMPUTE is four-way Form (Go/Rust/TS/fkwu); only host file IO is a carrier.
;
; ── THE NL→NL MODEL = A COMPOSITION (read native-translation-model.form first) ──
;   Translation src→tgt is nearest-meaning over a SHARED coordinate space, not a
;   pair-model. A FACE = (modality, surface, embedding). NL→NL is just both faces in
;   the NL modality. ONE engine carries every pair (O(M) faces, not O(M²) models).
;   The data — faces with meaning coordinates, and the learned weights — lives in
;   substrate cells OUTSIDE the recipe; the .fk files are only the engine. Editing
;   the model = changing cells (learning), never typing rows of source.
;
;   WHAT RUNS OFFLINE TODAY (proven four-way unless marked):
;     - RETRIEVAL translate (S2): translation-engine.fk — te-translate / te-nearest
;       map a source NL face to the nearest target-NL surface by L1 embedding
;       distance; generalises to unseen surfaces via te-translate-emb over a learned
;       query embedding. Band: tests/translation-engine-band.fk → 1111111 four-way.
;     - SUPERVISED training over a CORPUS: transformer-corpus-train.fk —
;       tct-train-blocks folds the proven two-block residual SGD atom
;       (transformer-backprop.fk) over a list of (x, t) pairs for N epochs;
;       tct-corpus-loss / tct-heldout-correct measure it. For NL→NL the pair is
;       (source-embedding, target-embedding): the model learns the encode→map→render
;       the design names. Bands: transformer-corpus-train 31, -wide 31, four-way —
;       dimension-generic (the 4×4 width proves it is not pinned to 2-dim).
;     - The numeric floor under both: transformer-numerics 4095, transformer-block
;       511, embedding-as-recipe (content-addressed float vectors, node_eq exact +
;       graded distance). embedding = a content-addressed COORDINATE — the feature
;       no other runtime has; identical meaning across surfaces interns to ONE NodeID.
;
;   GENERATION — the first rung RUNS (the S3 decoder in native-translation-model.form):
;     - neural-lm.fk + tests/neural-lm-band.fk → 31 FOUR-WAY. A LEARNED contextual
;       next-token model: the proven two-block residual stack trains (context-emb →
;       next-token-emb, the tct-train fold) and GENERATES by the content-address
;       SNAP the diffusion-decoder design names — predict a point in meaning-space,
;       snap to the NEAREST interned token cell (nl-render, the sequence-predictor
;       max-select spine), feed it back (nl-gen, autoregressive). On the 4-token
;       cyclic grammar a→b→c→d→a it trains to ~0 loss and emits the cycle
;       indefinitely. This replaces sequence-predictor.fk's Markov-1 COUNTS with a
;       learned model — generation, not retrieval.
;     - THE CLIMB (each a nameable band over proven cells): multi-token context via
;       full-T sequence self-attention (named-open in form-native-models.form — the
;       block is proven at T=1/T=2); learned DENSE embeddings replacing the seed
;       one-hots (the same engine over both); larger vocabulary + offline distillation
;       of the next-token targets from a LOCAL oracle (oracle-catalog.fk's ollama row)
;       via predictor-sampling.fk. The diffusion-snap decoder (ml-diffusion-model-flow.form)
;       is its own design-stage alternative to the autoregressive loop.
;
; ── THE COPYRIGHT GATE — "we cannot train on them", made enforceable ──
;   The legal boundary: copyright-restricted content may be USED FOR TESTING
;   (held-out evaluation — measuring the model's loss/quality on it) but its
;   examples must NEVER enter the SGD fold that updates weights. This is now a hard,
;   FAIL-CLOSED gate whose DECISION is a four-way Form recipe, not a convention a
;   human must remember.
;
;     - THE DECISION: form-stdlib/corpus-license-gate.fk — clg-phase routes a
;       corpus cell's PROVENANCE tag to "train" | "eval". Train-eligible ONLY for an
;       explicit lawful allowlist (clg-allow = owned / public-domain / permissive /
;       consented — DATA, append a row to extend). EVERYTHING ELSE — "copyright",
;       "all-rights-reserved", and any UNKNOWN/absent provenance — routes to
;       eval-only. Uncertainty never trains. Band: corpus-license-gate-band → 31
;       FOUR-WAY (string-tag matching, the op family cjk-channel crosses as fks); the
;       safety-critical bit (UNKNOWN is NOT train-eligible) is proven on every kernel.
;     - THE CARRIER: scripts/corpus_partition_by_license.sh — reads a corpus, asks
;       the Form gate to classify its distinct provenance tags (one kernel call),
;       and writes <stem>.train-eligible.jsonl + <stem>.eval-only.jsonl. The carrier
;       is file IO only; the boundary is decided by the recipe. It ABORTS if any
;       copyright row would leak into train-eligible.
;     - THE TEST PATH: form_cli_transformer_train_wide.sh's optional 4th arg
;       [eval-corpus] featurizes a separate corpus and reports the trained model's
;       loss on it — MEASURED, never folded. Pass the .eval-only (copyright) file here.
;
;   PROVENANCE lives on the corpus cell (a "license" / "provenance" field per row),
;   the same shape oracle-catalog.fk already carries trust = "local"|"remote-membrane"
;   and the consent membrane carries receipts. Untagged rows take an operator-declared
;   --default-license (e.g. the body's own captured turns are "owned"); with no
;   default they are "unknown" → eval-only (fail-closed). A row's own copyright tag
;   always wins over the default.
;
; ── THE SELF-LEARNING LOOP (proven end-to-end 2026-06-19) ──
;   ONE terminal command improves the model and keeps the best — the harness that walks
;   toward "usable for most tasks":
;     `bash scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh learn <corpus.jsonl> --rounds 3`
;   Each round: gate copyright OUT of the fold → train harder (more epochs) → measure
;   held-out accuracy → KEEP the model only if it beats the current champion. The accept
;   is champion-challenger (champion-challenger.fk): the WALK is the always-correct
;   champion; a trained model is a challenger that must EARN the slot by exceeding held-out.
;   The champion — the rising floor — PERSISTS (nl-champion.txt) across invocations, so
;   running `learn` again pushes the floor higher. PROVEN: round 1 promoted 16/24 held-out
;   (beat the unigram baseline 12/24), persisted; the floor is durable.
;   THE GRADIENT TO "MOST TASKS": the floor rises toward the bigram ceiling; the
;   ceiling-LIFTERS each plug into THIS SAME loop as they land — LM head + cross-entropy
;   (the biggest quality jump, fixes mean-regression), multi-token context (full-T
;   attention), dense learned embeddings, and offline distillation of next-token targets
;   from the LOCAL ollama oracle (oracle-catalog.fk — the mind coming home). Native speed
;   for deeper rounds arrives with fkwu's float self-JIT (one-acceleration-engine.form M0).
;
; ── THE RUNNABLE OFFLINE LOOP (proven end-to-end 2026-06-18) ──
;   TERMINAL ENTRYPOINT (no agent, no internet): scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh
;     `bash scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh`        prints the full instructions
;     `bash scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh check`  verifies offline prerequisites
;     `bash scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh learn <corpus.jsonl> --rounds 3`
;        the self-learning loop above (train → measure → keep-best → persist).
;     `bash scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh run <corpus.jsonl> --default-license owned`
;        does steps 1-2 below in one offline command. The steps are also runnable directly:
;   1. PARTITION by provenance (the gate splits lawful from test-only):
;        scripts/corpus_partition_by_license.sh <corpus.jsonl> --default-license owned
;      → <stem>.train-eligible.jsonl  +  <stem>.eval-only.jsonl
;   2. TRAIN on the lawful file ONLY, TEST on the copyright file:
;        scripts/form_cli_transformer_train_wide.sh \
;            <stem>.train-eligible.jsonl 60 200 <stem>.eval-only.jsonl
;      → train loss falls; held-out loss falls (generalisation within lawful data);
;        the copyright TEST loss is reported separately — measured, never trained.
;   3. RETRIEVAL translate at inference (S2), corpus passed as data:
;        translation-engine.fk te-translate over the faces (NL→NL by nearest meaning).
;   The featurizer here maps NL → a 4-dim signal vector as the worked example; the
;   NL→NL target is (source-embedding → target-embedding) over embedding-as-recipe
;   faces, the SAME fold (the recipe is dimension-generic).
;
; ── HONEST SEAM ──
;   COMPUTE is four-way Form: the gate decision, the SGD fold, the numerics, the
;   nearest-meaning retrieval. CARRIER is host-io (3-kernel standing wall): reading
;   corpus files, writing the partition files, persisting weights. Weights SHARE
;   without serialization — content-addressed by NodeID, like git objects by hash —
;   so a trained model is referenced, never byte-transferred; only cross-process
;   PERSISTENCE needs the host carrier. Carrier persists; engine proves;
;   content-address shares.
;
; KIN: native-translation-model.form (the design — S1-S4, diffusion, auto-ml) ·
;   translation-engine.fk + tests/translation-engine-band.fk (S2 retrieval) ·
;   transformer-corpus-train.fk + tests/transformer-corpus-train(-wide)-band.fk (the
;   fold) · neural-lm.fk + tests/neural-lm-band.fk (the first generative rung —
;   predict-in-meaning-space + content-address snap + autoregressive emit, four-way) ·
;   corpus-license-gate.fk + tests/corpus-license-gate-band.fk (the gate) ·
;   scripts/corpus_partition_by_license.sh + scripts/form_cli_transformer_train_wide.sh
;   (the carriers) · scripts/offline_nl_training_runbook.sh (the terminal teacher +
;   runner — no agent, no internet) · embedding-as-recipe.fk (content-addressed faces) ·
;   oracle-catalog.fk (local teachers, trust rows) · form-native-models.form (the
;   numeric floor + M1-M7 milestones) · preference-learning.form (a loss row that
;   prefers the vitality answer, orthogonal to this corpus path).
; teaching: lc-cognitive-sovereignty
